  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so it happened that Bernadotte didn't even ask his government for permission to bring us all in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He instead telephoned, or by some means got in touch with them quickly, and he asked them to send into northern Germany, to Ravensbruck concentration camp, vehicles that could carry the maximum amount of people-- ambulances, trucks, vans, buses, and so on-- and have them all painted white with red crosses on them, so that the Allies will not bomb them.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And so it happens-- happened that this rescue mission was called the White Fleet Rescue Mission.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They pulled into Ravensbruck concentration camp and they filled up-- them up with prisoners, and-- and he described that some of them were so sick they couldn't-- had to be carried onto ambulances-- ambulances and these vehicles-- and they were dying right there.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they were dying while-- while they were in the vehicles [CRYING] and I just remember these very, very real scenes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And while they were free already, they were dying, never had a chance to live their lives fully.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they-- and I thought that we were then taken to the harbor, but a few years ago, I learned that-- through research that, in fact, we were dropped on the Danish side, and these white-- the white fleet returned to carry more-- more of these inmates, still.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The white fleet rescue mission caught up with our train and-- and went from camp to camp nearby until it was full, and we were attached to the rescue mission, and we were liberated and taken to-- to Denmark.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was then carried on a stretcher onto-- out of this vehicle, and I told them I can walk, but they said to lie down.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
